To replicate:
1. Create a compound shape by adding two or more CollisionShape components to a node.
2. Wait for the next frame
3. Begin deleting shapes with node.RemoveComponent()
4. Engine will freeze when only 1 shape remains.

```
// First shape
shape_ = box_->CreateComponent<CollisionShape>();
shape_->SetBox(Vector3::ONE);

// Second shape
shape_ = box_->CreateComponent<CollisionShape>();
shape_->SetBox(Vector3::ONE);

// Trigger the freeze sometime later
box_->RemoveComponent(shape_);
```

Modified 11_Physics to show the problem
http://pasteall.org/504185

And I get this in debug mode
```
Assert colObjWrap->getCollisionShape()->isCompound() in line 244, file /home/user/repos/Urho3D/Source/ThirdParty/Bullet/src/BulletCollision/CollisionDispatch/btCompoundCollisionAlgorithm.cpp
Trace/breakpoint trap
```

EDIT
Workaround = remove the last 2 collision shapes at the same time and re-create the original.

Let it be here, but it may be Detour/Recast bug.

1. Open Sample 39
2. Change plane size and location:

```
    Vector3 mmin(-54.4f, 0, -54.4f);
    Vector3 mmax(51.2f, 0, 51.2f);
    planeNode->SetScale(mmax - mmin + Vector3::UP);
    planeNode->SetPosition((mmin + mmax) / 2);
```

3. Set tile size to 32

`navMesh->SetTileSize(32);`

4. Try to climb on the marked box

